The paper deals with Natural Language Inference (NLI), which is a subfield of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses experiments and analysis of NLI datasets, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a hypothesis-only model, which is a statistical approach to NLI, and discusses its performance, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of context in NLI, which can be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
